      content: 'This plan provides a concrete day-by-day framework for launching your Etsy printable shop from account creation through your first month of operations.\n\nDay 1 \u2014 account and branding: create your Etsy seller account, configure payment and tax information, design your shop logo and banner, write your About section, set up shop policies for digital downloads, and create 5 to 6 shop sections organized by product category.\n\nDay 2 to 4 \u2014 product creation: use your 3 to 5 selected generators to create your initial product inventory. Target 15 to 20 products across 3 to 4 popular themes (animals, food, seasons, holidays). Export every product as PDF in both Letter and A4 sizes. Generate answer keys for all worksheets. Create listing photos for each product.\n\nDay 5 to 6 \u2014 listing creation: write and publish all 15 to 20 initial listings with fully optimized titles, all 13 tags filled, professional descriptions, complete attributes, and listing photos. Upload digital files and verify the download process works correctly by purchasing a test listing if needed.\n\nDay 7 \u2014 launch verification: review all published listings for errors in titles, descriptions, pricing, and file attachments. Verify listing photos display correctly at thumbnail size. Share your shop link on personal social media and Pinterest. Set up a basic Pinterest board for your printable products.\n\nDay 8 to 14 \u2014 monitor, adjust, and add: check Etsy Stats daily. Revise titles and tags on zero-impression listings. Add 4 to 6 new listings based on search term data from Stats. Create Pinterest pins for your top products. Respond to any buyer messages within hours.\n\nDay 15 to 21 \u2014 optimize and expand: analyze two weeks of Stats data. Create variations of your best-performing products (new themes, difficulty levels, bundle combinations). Add 4 to 6 more listings. Consider running a 15% introductory sale on select listings to boost sales velocity.\n\nDay 22 to 30 \u2014 scale and review: push your total listing count toward 25 to 30 products. Create your first bundle listings combining individual products at premium prices. Include thank-you pages with review invitations in all product PDFs. Plan your month-two content calendar based on performance data from month one.',
